  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Supply Chain Executive",
  "description": "<p>Duties and Responsibilities includes, but not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Source and evaluate Suppliers to ensure quality, cost-effectiveness, and reliability</li>\n  <li>Request and analyse for quotes from Suppliers</li>\n  <li>Coordinate purchasing activities with Suppliers, Production, Quality and Engineers</li>\n  <li>Prepare and process purchase requisitions, purchase orders, and track order fulfillment</li>\n  <li>Negotiate pricing, terms, and delivery schedules with Suppliers</li>\n  <li>Maintain strong working relationships with Suppliers</li>\n  <li>Responsible for negotiating with Suppliers to ensure Company is always in an advantageous position</li>\n  <li>Responsible for input, accuracy and completeness of database information in Procurement and Supply Chain module (e.g. lead time, inventory turnover, price, etc.)</li>\n  <li>Monitor stock levels and management replenishment according to MRP to avoid shortages or overstocking</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with Productions, Sales and Store to align material availability with demand</li>\n  <li>Monitor the costs and schedules to ensure highest quality at best value</li>\n  <li>Interact closely with Suppliers and Engineer/QA to resolve quality issues</li>\n  <li>Plan and coordinate inbound and outbound shipments to ensure on-time delivery</li>\n  <li>Liaise with freight forwarders for import/export matters</li>\n  <li>Optimise transportation and warehouse operations for cost efficiency</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Supply Chain Management and at least 3 years’ experience in Supply Chain in similar industry</li>\n  <li>Familiar with import/export procedures and Incoterms</li>\n  <li>Chartered Institute of Procurement &amp; Supply (CIPS) or similar qualification</li>\n  <li>ERP and MRP knowledge is required</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
